-- Tottenham Eyes January Move for Real Madrid's Benzema: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2010-11-22T08:53:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/tottenham-eyes-january-move-for-real-madrid-s-benzema-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Redknapp ‘Tweaks’  Tottenham coach  Harry Redknapp  is exploring the possibility
of signing Real Madrid striker  Karim Benzema  on loan in January,
the  Daily Mail  reported.  Redknapp will make another bid for West Ham midfielder
 Scott Parker  and may offer  Niko Kranjcar  in part exchange for
Liverpool defender  Glen Johnson , the Mail said.  Redknapp said he’s looking to “tweak” his squad in what
he called “the most open season ever,” according to the Mail.  Houllier Move  Aston Villa coach  Gerard Houllier  is ready to make a 1.2
million-pound ($1.9 million) bid for Middlesbrough center-back
 David Wheater , the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Wheater’s contract expires at the end of the season and
Middlesbrough is willing to trade him in January, the Mirror
said.  MLS Striker  Seattle Sounders striker Steve Zakuani, a “huge hit” in
Major League Soccer, may play for Everton in the U.S. league’s
offseason, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The 22-year-old Congo national team player will start by
training with the northwest England club, the Mirror said.  Blackburn Stadium  The new owner of Blackburn plans to rename its Ewood Park
stadium for the first time since the 19th Century, the  Daily
Express  reported.  Venky’s (India) Ltd., which bought the club last week, may
rename the arena after its company or sell the naming rights,
the Express said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
